==English==

===Intransitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|inhal|e}}

# To draw air into the [[lung]]s through the nose or mouth by action of the [[diaphragm]].

====Synonyms====
*[[breathe in]], [[inspire]]

====Antonyms====
*[[breathe out]], [[exhale]], [[expire]] (''archaic'')

====Translations====
'''draw air into the lungs'''
{{top}}
*German: [[einatmen]]
*French: [[aspirer]]
*[[Ido]]: [[aspirar]]
{{mid}}
*Polish: [[wdychać]]
*Slovene: [[vdihovati]] / [[vdihniti]]
{{bottom}}

===Transitive verb===
{{en-infl-reg-other-e|inhal|e}}

# To draw (something, a medicament) into the nose or lungs by action of the [[diaphragm]].

====Synonyms====
*[[breathe in]], [[inspire]]

====Antonyms====
*[[breathe out]], [[exhale]]

====Translations====
'''to draw somethin into the node or lungs'''
{{top}}
*German: [[inhalieren]]
{{mid}}
*Polish: [[inhalować]], [[wziewać]]
{{bottom}}

